{
  "texts": [
    "Several frameworks are specialized in designing, compiling and optimizing such pipelines.",
    "Sample features of those pipelines include tool calling (allowing the generative AI system to invoke external services as part of the response generation process, e.g., OpenAI Code Interpreter or LangChain tool calling agents), knowledge bases (collections of documents from which the relevant snippets for a given task can be retrieved [49]) and agents (AI-based systems that can decompose complex goals into a collection of simpler subtasks which may include tool calling and accessing knowledge bases, e.g., [50,51]).In this direction, DSPy [52,53] is a Python framework that enables the composition and optimization of applications based on text-to-text models.",
    "Similarly, Semantic Kernel [54] is a framework to orchestrate different AI services to solve complex tasks.",
    "To this end, it creates a plan that may require invoking different components as plugins.",
    "Moreover, the previously mentioned LangChain library also offers an agent framework."
  ]
}